To mount the BusAdapter, follow these steps:

* To connect a wire without tools, strip 8 to 10 mm of the wires and insert the cable into the push-in terminal as far as it will go. Then, push the wired connector plug into the plug socket of the interface module (page_number: 100, parent_section_hierarchy: 8.11 Connecting the 3DI/LC module for the motor starter > Tool-free connection of cables: single-wire without end sleeve, multi-wire (stranded) with end sleeve or ultrasonically sealed)
* You can also watch a video sequence for proper connection at https://support.automation.siemens.com/WW/view/en/95886218
* However, it's not necessary to remove the BusAdapter from the IM 155-6 PN R1 interface modules (page_number: 61-62, parent_section_hierarchy: 7.4 Installing ET 200SP R1 > Removing the ET 200SP R1 system > NOTE)
* The only tool required for mounting and removing the BusAdapter is a 3 to 3.5 mm screwdriver (page_number: 59, page_number: 60, parent_section_hierarchy: 7.3 Mounting the CPU/interface module > Required tools)

Note that you should not remove the motor starter for an extended period without following proper procedures and ensuring dust protection and mechanical durability are maintained.
